    <item>
      <title>Export data from MongoDB</title>
      <link>https://benmatselby.dev/tidbits/mongodb/export-data/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 12 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://benmatselby.dev/tidbits/mongodb/export-data/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;To export data from MongoDB, you can use the &lt;code&gt;mongoexport&lt;/code&gt; command. This command&#xA;allows you to export data from a MongoDB collection into a JSON or CSV file.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#d0d0d0;background-color:#202020;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-shell&#34; data-lang=&#34;shell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;mongoexport --db=my-database --collection=user --type=csv --fields=_id &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ed9d13&#34;&gt;\&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  --query=&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ed9d13&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;{&amp;#34;status&amp;#34;: &amp;#34;active&amp;#34;}&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; --out=/tmp/users.csv &lt;span style=&#34;color:#40ffff&#34;&gt;$MONGO_URI&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Get an explain plan for a query</title>
      <link>https://benmatselby.dev/tidbits/mongodb/get-an-explain-plan/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 12 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://benmatselby.dev/tidbits/mongodb/get-an-explain-plan/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;To get an explain plan for a query in MongoDB, you can use the &lt;code&gt;explain()&lt;/code&gt; method.&#xA;This method provides information about the execution of a query, including the&#xA;stages of the query and the indexes used.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#d0d0d0;background-color:#202020;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-shell&#34; data-lang=&#34;shell&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;db.user.find({status: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ed9d13&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;active&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;}).explain()&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Get the timestamp from a MongoDB ObjectId</title>
      <link>https://benmatselby.dev/tidbits/mongodb/get-timestamp-from-objectid/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 12 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://benmatselby.dev/tidbits/mongodb/get-timestamp-from-objectid/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;When you want to extract the timestamp from a MongoDB ObjectId, you can use the following method:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#d0d0d0;background-color:#202020;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-javascript&#34; data-lang=&#34;javascript&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6ab825;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; objectId = &lt;span style=&#34;color:#6ab825;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ObjectId(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ed9d13&#34;&gt;&amp;#39;yourObjectIdHere&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#6ab825;font-weight:bold&#34;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; timestamp = objectId.getTimestamp();&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;console.log(timestamp);&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#d0d0d0;background-color:#202020;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-javascript&#34; data-lang=&#34;javascript&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;ObjectId().getTimestamp();&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;This will give you the timestamp of when the ObjectId was created.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
